OPPORTUNITY MOVE
----------------
IF SOME ACTION POINTS ARE SAVED BEFORE ENDING A PLAYERS TURN,DURING THE
ENEMYS TURN AN OPPORTUNITY MOVE MAY BE AWARDED, AN OPPORTUNITY MOVE OCCURS
IF A PLAYER HAS MORE THAN 5 ACTION POINTS,AND CAN BE SEEN BY THE
OPPOSITION. THE NUMBER OF ACTION POINTS SAVES DETERMINES THE CHANCE OF
BEING AWARDED AN OPPORTUNITY MOVE;SAVING 20 OR MORE ACTION POINTS GIVES A
100% CHANCE,DECREASING TOWARDS 0% AS LESS ACTION POINTS ARE SAVED.DURING AN
OPPORTUNITY MOVE CONTROL IS TAKEN FROM THE ENEMY AND THE PLAYER CONCERNED
IS GIVEN A CHANCE TO USE HIS REMAINING ACTION POINTS. ENDING HIS TURN GIVES
CONTROL BACK TO THE ENEMY. ONLY ONE OPPORTUNITY MOVE MAY BE AWARDED PER
GAME TURN.

